notesStmt.note: 885 leaves foliated (Part 1) 1-195, (Part 2) 1-479, 482-691, [i], upper left and lower right verso.

Mistakes covered over in yellow or blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins; significant syllables, words, or phrases highlighted in red throughout; vertical margins marked with double red line.
This manuscript is accompanied by two wooden boards with beveled edges used for supporting the manuscript and a large orange canvas wrapper to protect the manuscript.
Watermarks of Britannia; the name W. & J. Harris, Turkey Mill, 1839; and J. & J. Town, Turkey Mill, 1840.

msContents.summary: A treatise on Advaita (non-dualism) philosophy that is distinct from Vedānta. Addresses the concept of liberation (nirvāṇa) for non-ascetics. It is a Kashmiri work and part of the Mokṣopāya (f. 691r). It became the basis of the Yogavāsiṣṭha, a work of Vedānta philosophy. An unidentified commentary runs horizontally above and below the root text.

msItem.colophon: Colophon: iti śrīmahārāmāyaṇe mokṣopāye nirvāṇaprakaraṇe uttarārdhe bālakāṃḍe devadūtokte śatasahasryāṃ saṃhitāyāṃ vāsiṣṭe brahmadarśane ekonaviṃśatyuttaradviśatatamaḥ sargaḥ 239 iti nirvāṇaprakaraṇaṃ saṃpūṇamastu // (f. 691r).
